text: Kieran Collins (born 14 December 1997) is a former Australian rules footballer who played for the Western Bulldogs in the Australian Football League (AFL). He was drafted by the Western Bulldogs with their second selection and twenty- sixth overall in the 2015 national draft. He made his debut in the twenty-five point loss against in round 9, 2016 at the Spotless Stadium. Collins was delisted at the end of 2018. http://www.afl.com.au/news/2018-08-28/dogs- delisted-two-more-leave-the-kennel He signed to play with the Northern Blues in the Victorian Football League in 2019. ==References== ==External links== * * Category:1997 births Category:Living people Category:People educated at Haileybury, Melbourne Category:Western Bulldogs players Category:Dandenong Stingrays players Category:Australian rules footballers from Victoria (Australia)
